ll, "default": null}, {"name": "gradient_stack", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "rotation_angle_deg", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "seismod1d.model.stack.get_angle_stack", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "traces", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "theta", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "angle_min", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "angle_max", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "seismod1d.model.stack.get_avo_stacks", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "traces", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "theta", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "avo_stack_opt", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "seismod1d.model.synthetics", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "seismod1d.model.synthetics.make_traces", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "RT", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "RC", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "ww_t", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "ww_a", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "tmin", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "tmax", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Input reflection coefficients for multiple trace, convolve with wavelet and\noutput synthetic seismogram\n\nArgs:\n    RT (2D array): Time of each reflection event. Columns are separate traces\n    (angle/offset). Rows represents reflection surfaces.\n    RC (2D array): Reflection coefficients. Same size as above array.\n    ww_t (1D array): Wavelet time vector (assumes even sampling)\n    ww_a (1D array): Wavelet amplitude vector\n    tmin (value): optional output minimum time\n    tmax (value): optional output maximum time\nReturns:\n    TR (2D array): Synthetic seismogram.", "import bravos.domainutils.reflectivity_vti as reflectivity_vti"]}, {"name": "seismod1d.model.synthetics.conv_single_trace", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "rc_t", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "rc_v", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "fv", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "ww_af", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Convolve a series of discrete reflection coeficients with a wavelet to\n obtain a seismic trace, by multiplying their frequency spectra.\n\nArgs:\n    rc_t (ndarray): The time of each reflection coefficient (s)\n    rc_v (ndarray): The reflection coefficients (possibly complex values)\n    fv (ndarray): Frequency vector\n    ww_af (ndarray): The wavelet in frequency domain\nReturns:\n    tr_f: (ndarray): Seismic trace in frequency domain"]}, {"name": "seismod1d.model.synthetics.apply_phase_rot", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "TR", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "seismod1d.model.synthetics.display_traces", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "xx", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "tt", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "traces", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "xlim", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "ylim", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "xlabel", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "seismod1d.model.synthetics._apply_along_axis", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "func_1d", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "arr", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Apply 1D function across 2D slice as efficiently as possible.\n\nAlthough `np.apply_along_axis` seems to do well enough, map usually\nseems to end up beig a bit faster.\n\nArgs:\n: func_1d (function): the 1D function to apply, e.g. np.convolve. Should\n\n  : take 2 or more arguments: the\n\nExample\n\\>>> apply_along_axes(np.convolve, reflectivity_2d, wavelet, mode='same')\n"]}, {"name": "seismod1d.model.synthetics._rotate_phase", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "w", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "phi", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "degrees", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Performs a phase rotation of wavelet or wavelet bank using:\n\n$$\nA = w(t)\\cos\\phi - h(t)\\sin\\phi\n$$\n\nwhere `w(t)` is the wavelet, `h(t)` is its Hilbert transform, and phi is\nthe phase rotation angle (default is radians).\n\nThe analytic signal can be written in the form $S(t) = A(t)e^{j\\theta (t)}$\nwhere $A(t) = \\left| h(w(t)) \\right|$ and $\\theta(t) = \\tan^{-1}[h(w(t))]$.\n`A(t)` is called the \"reflection strength\" and $\\phi(t)$ is called the \"instantaneous\nphase\".\n\nA constant phase rotation $\\phi$ would produce the analytic signal\n$S(t)=A(t)e^{j(\\theta(t) + \\phi)}$. To get the non-analytic signal,\nwe take\n\n$$\nreal(S(t)) &= A(t)\\cos(\\theta(t) + \\phi) \\\\\n&= A(t)\\cos\\theta(t)\\cos(\\phi)-\\sin\\theta(t)\\sin(\\phi))\\\\\n&= w(t)\\cos\\phi-h(t)\\sin\\phi\n$$\n\nArgs:\n\n: w (ndarray): The wavelet vector, can be a 2D wavelet bank.\n  phi (float): The phase rotation angle (in radians) to apply.\n  degrees (bool): If phi is in degrees not radians.\n\nReturns:\n\n: The phase rotated signal (or bank of signals).\n"]}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "seismod1d.model.SynthModel", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "seismod1d.model.SynthModel.NSPACE", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "seismod1d.model.SynthModel.SynthModel", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "seismod1d.model.SynthModel.SynthModel.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "depth", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "vp", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "vs", "type": null, "default":