eful because we can pass arrays to it, which we can't do to\nscattering_matrix().\n\nDvorkin et al. (2014). Seismic Reflections of Rock Properties. Cambridge.\n\nReturns the complex reflectivity.\n\nArgs:\n    vp1 (ndarray): The upper P-wave velocity; float or 1D array length m.\n    vs1 (ndarray): The upper S-wave velocity; float or 1D array length m.\n    rho1 (ndarray): The upper layer's density; float or 1D array length m.\n    vp2 (ndarray): The lower P-wave velocity; float or 1D array length m.\n    vs2 (ndarray): The lower S-wave velocity; float or 1D array length m.\n    rho2 (ndarray): The lower layer's density; float or 1D array length m.\n    theta1 (ndarray): The incidence angle; float or 1D array length n.\n\nReturns:\n    ndarray. The exact Zoeppritz solution for P-P reflectivity at the\n        interface. Will be a float (for float inputs and one angle), a\n        1 x n array (for float inputs and an array of angles), a 1 x m\n        array (for float inputs and one angle), or an n x m array (for\n        array inputs and an array of angles)."]}, {"name": "seismod1d.model.reflectivity_iso.get_zoeppritz_rpp", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "vp", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "vs", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "rho", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "reflection_angles", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "apply_tr_loss", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "seismod1d.model.reflectivity_iso.get_zoeppritz", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "vp", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "vs", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "rho", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "reflection_angles", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "seismod1d.model.reflectivity_vti", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "seismod1d.model.reflectivity_vti.conv_vti_tho